definitions.definition: The state or quality of being palatalized , of pronouncing a sound with the tongue against the palate of the mouth that normally is not.
An instance of pronunciation in which a sound is palatalized.

main_definition: ( phonology , uncountable ) The state or quality of being palatalized , of pronouncing a sound with the tongue against the palate of the mouth that normally is not.
secondary_definitions: ( phonology , countable ) An instance of pronunciation in which a sound is palatalized.
